                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="attenborough_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(1923-2014) an English film actor, producer and director. He acted in many famous British films, including <span class="ebi">Brighton Rock</span> (1947). His most successful film as director and producer was <span class="ebi">Gandhi</span> (1982), which won eight <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/oscartm" title="Oscars definition"><span class="ndv">Oscars</span></a>. He was made a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/knight_1" title="knight definition"><span class="ndv">knight</span></a> in 1976 and a <span class="ndv" href="lifepeer_d_1" tofix="" xt="andv">life peer</span> in 1993. David Attenborough is his brother.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
